<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idac4dae40-47c4-11f1-8df3-c75a02f6a58e" identifier="/us/usc/t1/s103"><num value="103">§ 103.</num><heading> Enacting or resolving words after first section</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No enacting or resolving words shall be used in any section of an Act or resolution of Congress except in the first.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idac4dae41-47c4-11f1-8df3-c75a02f6a58e">(<ref href="/us/act/1947-07-30/ch388">July 30, 1947, ch. 388</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/61/634">61 Stat. 634</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
